During the course, the students learn about central legal terms and legal areas, analyse the structure of legal texts and language (vocabulary, morphological and syntactic characteristics) used in respective foreign languages and in Estonian, and practice translating legal texts from a foreign language into Estonian and from Estonian into a foreign language.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the skills of translating LSP-texts on law from the foreign language into Estonian and vice versa. During the seminars, students acquire the principles of preparatory analysis of texts and learn different translation strategies and methods for achieving the aim of the translation task. Students enhance their command of business terminology in Estonian as well as in the foreign language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - After successful completion of the course you have acquired the skills of functional analysis of legal texts in Estonian and the foreign language.
- Depending on text analysis results, you are able to choose the appropriate translation strategy for carrying out the translation task.
- You have experience in translating different text types from the foreign language into Estonian and vice versa.
- You are able to find the necessary information for translation, to work with parallel texts and Internet databases.
- You have acquired the fundamentals of legal terminology necessary for professional translation.
